  <p class="research-subtitle">Who we are, how we work, and how to reach us.</p>
  <div class="research-grid">

    <div class="research-card">
      <div class="research-card-icon">◎</div>
      <h3 class="research-card-title">Our Mission</h3>
      <p class="research-card-desc">The Epoch Institute studies civilisational patterns through data-driven research — examining how empires rise, sustain themselves, and collapse, and what those trajectories reveal about the forces that shape human societies. We make history intellectually rigorous and genuinely accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="research-card">
      <div class="research-card-icon">⊞</div>
      <h3 class="research-card-title">Methodology</h3>
      <p class="research-card-desc">Empire power scores are researcher-assigned normalised indices (0–10) across six dimensions: territory, military capacity, economic output, administrative coherence, cultural influence, and geopolitical reach. All scores are drawn from peer-reviewed historiography and cited using Harvard-style references. Each trajectory is scaled to its own peak, allowing comparison of shape rather than absolute size.</p>
    </div>

